TOP 7 IMPORTANT FILES - ChessWeb2.8 (NeonGambit)
For Diploma Documentation

Project Type:
Full-stack chess platform (React + TypeScript frontend, Node.js + Express + Socket.IO backend)

Most Important Core Part:
server/index.js
Reason: This file is the realtime game server (matchmaking, move validation, game rooms, friend challenges, game over handling, and API mounting).

============================================================
1) FRONTEND ENTRY POINT
File: src/main.tsx
Why it matters:
Bootstraps the whole React app into the DOM.

Key Code:
import { StrictMode } from "react";
import { createRoot } from "react-dom/client";
import "./index.css";
import App from "./App.tsx";

createRoot(document.getElementById("root")!).render(
  <StrictMode>
    <App />
  </StrictMode>
);

============================================================
2) MAIN APP ROUTING + ACCESS CONTROL
File: src/App.tsx
Why it matters:
Defines all application routes, protected pages, public pages, layout behavior, theme control, and auth checks.

Key Code:
function ProtectedRoute({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const { isAuthenticated, isLoading } = useAuthStore();
  const location = useLocation();
  if (isLoading) return <div className="...animate-spin" />;
  if (!isAuthenticated) {
    return <Navigate to="/login" state={{ from: location }} replace />;
  }
  return <>{children}</>;
}

function App() {
  return (
    <Router future={{ v7_startTransition: true, v7_relativeSplatPath: true }}>
      <ThemeController />
      <AuthChecker />
      <RealtimeBridge />
      <Layout>
        <Routes>
          <Route path="/" element={<ProtectedRoute><Dashboard /></ProtectedRoute>} />
          <Route path="/play" element={<ProtectedRoute><Game /></ProtectedRoute>} />
          <Route path="/play/quick" element={<ProtectedRoute><QuickMatch /></ProtectedRoute>} />
          <Route path="/play/friend" element={<ProtectedRoute><PlayWithFriend /></ProtectedRoute>} />
        </Routes>
      </Layout>
    </Router>
  );
}

============================================================
3) AUTH STATE + AUTH API CLIENT
File: src/store/authStore.ts
Why it matters:
Central user session state (Zustand) + login/register/logout/getMe API calls used by the whole app.

Key Code:
export const useAuthStore = create<AuthState>()(
  persist(
    (set) => ({
      user: null,
      isAuthenticated: false,
      isLoading: true,
      setUser: (user) =>
        set({ user, isAuthenticated: !!user, isLoading: false, banReason: null }),
      logout: () => set({ user: null, isAuthenticated: false, banReason: null }),
    }),
    { name: "auth-storage" },
  ),
);

export const authApi = {
  async login(email: string, password: string, rememberMe = false) {
    const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/api/login`, {
      method: "POST",
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      credentials: "include",
      body: JSON.stringify({ email, password, rememberMe }),
    });
    const data = await res.json();
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error(data.error || "Login failed");
    return data;
  },
};

============================================================
4) BOT GAME CORE LOGIC (STOCKFISH MODE)
File: src/hooks/useStockfishGame.ts
Why it matters:
Core game logic for player-vs-bot mode: chess state, engine moves, pre-moves, promotion, timers, game-over flow, and history saving.

Key Code:
export function useStockfishGame() {
  const [game, setGame] = useState(() => new Chess());
  const gameRef = useRef<Chess>(game);
  const [gameStarted, setGameStarted] = useState(false);
  const [gameOver, setGameOver] = useState(false);
  const [moves, setMoves] = useState<string[]>([]);

  const engineRef = useStockfishEngine(
    gameSettings.difficulty,
    gameSettings.selectedBot,
  );

  const { isEngineThinking, makeEngineMove, handleEngineMessage } =
    useEngineMoves(
      engineRef,
      gameRef,
      playerColor,
      gameSettings.difficulty,
      gameOver,
      setGame,
      setMoves,
      setLastMove,
      tryApplyPreMove,
    );
}

============================================================
5) ONLINE QUICK MATCH (RANDOM OPPONENT)
File: src/hooks/useOnlineQuickMatch.ts
Why it matters:
Implements realtime multiplayer quick match using Socket.IO: queueing, match found, move sync, game over, rematch/cancel/resign.

Key Code:
const socket = io(SOCKET_URL, { withCredentials: true });

socket.on("queued", () => {
  setIsSearching(true);
  setQueueStatus("Searching for opponent...");
});

socket.on("matchFound", (payload: MatchFoundPayload) => {
  const nextGame = new Chess(payload.fen);
  setGame(nextGame);
  setGameId(payload.gameId);
  setPlayerColor(payload.color);
  setGameStarted(true);
});

socket.on("moveApplied", (payload: MoveAppliedPayload) => {
  if (payload.gameId !== gameIdRef.current) return;
  // sync move state from server
});

============================================================
6) FRIEND CHALLENGE ONLINE GAME FLOW
File: src/hooks/useFriendOnlineGame.ts
Why it matters:
Handles direct friend games with challenge acceptance, live board synchronization, premoves, and game result processing.

Key Code:
socket.on("friendGameStarted", (payload: FriendGameStartedPayload) => {
  applyFriendGameStart(payload);
});

socket.on("moveApplied", (payload: MoveAppliedPayload) => {
  if (payload.gameId !== gameIdRef.current) return;
  // apply incoming move and update turn
});

socket.on("gameOver", (payload: GameOverPayload) => {
  if (payload.gameId !== gameIdRef.current) return;
  setGameOver(true);
  setShowGameOverModal(true);
  setGameResult(formatResult(payload));
});

============================================================
7) BACKEND SERVER + SOCKET GAME ENGINE (MOST IMPORTANT)
File: server/index.js
Why it matters:
Single most important file for backend runtime. It mounts APIs, connects DB, handles realtime multiplayer events, matchmaking, and game lifecycle.

Key Code:
const app = express();
const server = http.createServer(app);
const io = new Server(server, {
  cors: { origin: ["http://localhost:5173", "http://127.0.0.1:5173"], credentials: true },
});

app.use("/api", authRoutes);
app.use("/api/history", historyRoutes);
app.use("/api/puzzles", puzzleRoutes);

io.on("connection", (socket) => {
  socket.on("findMatch", async ({ name, timeControl, variant }) => {
    // matchmaking queue logic + room creation
  });

  socket.on("makeMove", ({ gameId, from, to, promotion }) => {
    // server validates move, updates chess state, emits moveApplied/gameOver
  });
});

server.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);
});

